components.gb_investment.promotion.title: Promotion message
components.gb_investment.tutorial.welcom:
The purpose of this tutorial is to explain all the features of this tool.

You can click the below links to learn more about them.
To continue with the tutorial please click on "@:(utils.Next)" button.
components.gb_investment.tutorial.rush_1: @:(foe_data.gb.The_Arc) is a GB that gives a bonus that increases the rewards you get by placing in the top 5 on someone's GB. More the level of the Arc is high, more the reward are important. That's how we started talking about 1.8, 1.9, etc. In reality, this is the Arc bonus. In fact, 1.0 represents the basic reward, 1.8 represents the reward with an Arc level 70 (it gives 80% more reward at that level) and 1.9 represents the reward with an Arc level 80 (90% more reward). Threads exclusively reserved for this type of investment were created in guilds and groups of friends. This is based on the principle of "I give what I get", thus limiting conflicts between guild members or friends by not making profits on their GBs. Unlike endless threads (10, 50, 100, etc.), the other advantage of 1.8, 1.9, etc. threads is that it saves a considerable amount of time for the GB owner. This is because the owner only needs to put in the necessary number of FPs to secure places that are going to be taken by level 80 Arcs (in the case of thread 1.9). Let's take an example: Let's imagine that you want to raise your @:(foe_data.gb.Observatory) from level 10 to 60 and that you earn {fp50} per day. The total cost of the levels is {fp64975}. If you are using endless threads, your investment will be 1:1, i.e. {fp25} invested on a GB = {fp25} that another player will invest on your GB. So you will have to invest {fp37320} to reach level 60. At {fp50} per day, it will take you 2 years and 17 days. Now, if you use a 1.9 thread, you will have to only invest {fp12363} to reach level 60, so a saving of {fp24957} !. Still with {fp50} per day, you go from 2 years and 17 days to 8 months and 5 days !
Snipe is when a player takes a place on a GB in order to make a profit, usually not meeting the owner's expectations.

For example level 49 → 50 of the GB "@:(foe_data.gb.The_Virgo_Project)" does not require any FPs from the owner to secure the first two places. The expected investment at 1.9 is {fp1739}. A sniper (with an Arc level 80) could wait until the level opens to take his place directly and put {fp1679}, which would secure his place and make a profit of {fp60}.
components.gb_investment.tutorial.displa:
This tool gives you all the information the owner and investors need to know to invest on a level of a GB. It has two display modes: 

"@:(routes.gb_investment.tab.owner_view.title)" (where you are) which displays information only on the current level and in great detail.

"@:(routes.gb_investment.tab.investors_view.title)" displays the values of several levels in tabular form. You will only find the number of FPs that the owner and the investors have to put in with the resulting profit/loss.

The messages follow a template. You can import a template from the "@:(components.import_promotion_message.title)" tab or create your own from the "@:(components.promotion_message_builder.title)" tab.

foe_data.bonus.support_pool_bonus.gb_des: Raises your guild's support pool bonus, adds up with every building.

foe_data.bonus.aid_goods.gb_description: Produces 1 random good when aiding another player's city (manually motivating/polishing them also counts as aiding). The age of the random good corresponds to the age of the building you are aiding.
foe_data.bonus.plunder_goods.name: Plunder Goods
foe_data.bonus.plunder_goods.gb_descript: Produces random goods for up to 3 neighbors with each collect when plundering another player's city. The age of the random goods corresponds to the age of the building you are plundering.
foe_data.bonus.contribution_boost.name: Contribution Boost
foe_data.bonus.contribution_boost.gb_des: Raises the Forge Points, Medals, and Blueprints you receive from donation rewards.
foe_data.bonus.aid_blueprints.name: Aid Blueprints
foe_data.bonus.aid_blueprints.gb_descrip: Raises the chance of obtaining a blueprint when aiding another player's city (manually motivating/polishing them also counts as aiding). I.E. Having a 100% bonus will double your chance of finding a blueprint.
foe_data.bonus.relic_hunt.name: Relic Hunt
foe_data.bonus.relic_hunt.gb_description: This ability gives you the possibility to receive Relics on the Guild Expedition map whenever you successfully solve an encounter. Relics are very valuable and can appear in 3 different rarities. Each level increases the chance to find a Relic but also the odds to find an uncommon or rare Relic, as opposed to a common one.
foe_data.bonus.critical_hit.name: Critical Hit
foe_data.bonus.critical_hit.gb_descripti: Gives all units the chance of dealing 1.5 times the expected damage when attacking units of the same era. Critical hit also works against Reactive Armor (if expected damage is 4-4, a critical hit will do 6-6 damage). Rogues (and other no-age units) are not affected/cannot use this ability until they transform into another unit. A critical hit doing at least 11 damage will one-hit kill any unit, even with the morale bonus. This bonus applies to all attacking armies plus your defending army in PvP. The critical hit will not happen when a unit is retaliating.
foe_data.bonus.helping_hands.name: Helping Hands
foe_data.bonus.helping_hands.gb_descript: Gives you a certain chance to get a random resource when aiding another player's city (manually motivating/polishing them also counts as aiding). You can recieve goods from your current age, supplies, coins, medals, or even Diamonds.
foe_data.bonus.plunder_and_pillage.name: Plunder and Pillage
foe_data.bonus.plunder_and_pillage.gb_de: Gives you a certain chance to get double the resources when you plunder a neighbor's city after successfully defeating their defenses. It will double all resources that you can plunder, including Forge Points and Guild Power.
foe_data.bonus.first_strike.name: First Strike
foe_data.bonus.first_strike.gb_descripti: Gives you a chance that at the start of the next several fights, a unit from the enemy's defense army will be killed immediately. This only applies to the first wave of a battle.
foe_data.bonus.double_collection.name: Double Collection
foe_data.bonus.double_collection.gb_desc: Gives you a chance to get double the resources in the the first buildings collected. Excludes military and great buildings. Refreshes with each collection of this building.
foe_data.bonus.exploration_site.name: Exploration Site
